19/02/2013 - v1.0-alpha
	* ADDED: command line interface;
	* ADDED: Encrypt/Decrypt with AES256-CBC + MAC (Encrypt-then-MAC, HMAC+SHA512);
	* ADDED: secure file deletion after encryption;

23/05/2013 - v1.0-beta
	* IMPROVED: general code improvement;
	* IMPROVED: using gcrypt for random bytes generation; openssl dropped
	* FIXED: bugs [if any];
	* FIXED: compilation warning on Gentoo

24/05/2013 - v1.0-rc
	* removed custom header;
	* minor fixes;

28/05/2013 - v1.0.0
	* NEWSTABLE RELEASE :)

23/01/2014 - v1.1.0-alpha
	* ADDED: RMD160, MD5, TIGER, TIGER1, TIGER2, SHA-1, SHA224, SHA256, SHA384, SHA512, WHIRLPOOL
	* IMPROVED: better error reporting;
	
26/01/2014 - v1.1.0-beta
	* ADDED: documentation;
	* FIXED: bugs [if any];

07/03/2014 - v2.0.1
	* ADDED: GTK+3 interface;
	* ADDED: translation;
	* IMPROVED: error handling and reporting;
	* IMPROVED: documentation;
	* IMPROVED: using mmap for better performance
	* REMOVED: tiger1, tiger2, sha224, sha384, rmd160
	* FIXED: various bugs;

26/03/2014 - v2.1.0
	* ADDED: GOST94
	* ADDED: SHA3-256
	* ADDED: SHA3-512
	* IMPROVED: hash are computed using threads
	* ADDED: support for single or multiple encryption (aes, twofish, serpent, aes+twofish, aes+serpent, aes+twofish+serpent)
	* REMOVED: cli

27/03/2014 - v2.1.1
	* REMOVED: multiple encryption (it isn't really useful)

??/05/2014 - v2.2.0
	* ADDED: possibility to choose between file/text encryption
	* ADDED: data compression using zlib
	* ADDED: multiple file selection for en/de/cryption

??/??/2014 - v2.3.0
	* ADDED: asymmetric encryption support (with RSA or with a ECC algo)
	* AES256-ctr as default instead of AES256-cbc

?????????? - EVALUATING FEATURES
	* possibility to choose different aes mode like aes-cbc, aes-ctr, aes-gcm, etc
